section.def:
board
                (董事會) means a board of directors of a credit
            union constituted under section 28;

League
                (協會) means the Credit Union League of Hong Kong
            incorporated under Part XI;

Registrar
                (註冊官) means the Registrar of Credit Unions
            appointed under section 82;

paragraph.content:
determine the maximum number of shares which may be held by any one member,
                    which shall not without the permission of the board exceed twenty per cent of
                    the shares of the credit union and which shall apply to all members;

determine the maximum length of time in respect of which loans made by the
                    credit union to its members may remain outstanding, in whole or in
                    part;

shall carry out an examination of the affairs and audit the accounts of the
                credit union and prepare a balance sheet on the accounts at least once in each
                quarter of every financial year;

shall make or provide for an annual audit of the accounts of the credit union
                and submit a report thereon together with a balance sheet to the annual meeting of
                the credit union for its approval;
